<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="203" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d203">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Thornton</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-12-04"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 4, 1868.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received from Maria A. Lynch, the
                            sister of Robert B. Lynch, who is now undergoing sentence of
                            imprisonment in the penitentiary at Kingston, Canada, a letter of the
                            30th ultimo, a copy of which accompanies this note.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to express the hope that you will commend the inclosed
                            statement to the kind consideration of her Majesty’s authorities, and to
                            be, with the highest consideration, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Edward Thornton,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>